Suspected gas leak at Chinese factory affects 160 . About 160 people were treated in hospital in the southern Chinese city of Guangzhou after a suspected gas leak at a steel plant , Hong Kong media reported on Sunday . Hong Kong government radio quoted a spokesman for the Guangzhou Steel Corp as saying 80 of the people , mainly plant workers , were kept in hospital on Saturday night after the incident . The plant had been temporarily shut down and the company was investigating , he said . 
